<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1350,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,1389,1415]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[356,443,1390,1415]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="19">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[460,533,1390,1416]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,272,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,351,1358]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[236,1350,351,1358]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. External appearance of Perittia species. Fig. 1. P. mucronata 3 (Turkey: Aksehir region); Fig. 2. P. mucronata ♀ (Turkey: Aksehir region); Fig. 3. P. huemeri holotype 3 (Croatia); Fig. 4. P. huemeri ♀ (Hungary); Fig. 5. P. junnilaisella sp. n., 3 holotype; Fig. 6. P. junnilaisella sp. n., 3 paratype (Turkey: Aksehir region)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190274/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[515,533,1390,1416]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
): Forewing length 
<quantity box="[755,826,1390,1416]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
. Length of labial palpus 
<number box="[1116,1153,1390,1416]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" value="0.6">0.6</number>
times diameter of head; second segment weakly ascending, otherwise drooping, pale ochreous. Head, neck tuft, scape and pedicel of antenna white, flagellum grey, scape with pecten consisting of dense row of white stiff scales. Tegula and thorax white. Legs white with pale ochreous tibia and tarsal segments. Forewing broad lanceolate, unicolorous snow white, with concolorous fringe scales. Underside of forewing pale grey, fringe scales white. Hindwing pale grey above and below, fringe scales white. 
<emphasis box="[853,1055,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="19">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1073,1163,1583,1609]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 - 24" captionStartId="11.[151,271,1447,1471]" captionTargetBox="[257,1323,197,1419]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[248,1340,197,1423]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 22 - 24. Female genitalia of Perittia species. Fig. 22. P. mucronata (Turkey: Aksehir region, L. Kaila prep. 3915); Fig. 23. P. huemeri (Hungary, L. Kaila prep. 4348); Fig. 24. P. r a v i d a sp. n. (Greece: Kos, L. Kaila prep. 4544)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190281/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[1129,1163,1583,1609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
): Papillae anales fused dorsodistally with non-elastic membrane, distally tapered to joined sclerotised apex, basally with long setae; membranous sac between papillae anales ventrodistally, armed with coarse teeth forming a row of large teeth at cephalic end. Apophyses posteriores 
<number box="[629,667,1699,1725]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times longer than papillae anales, straight and stout; apophyses anteriores less than 
<number box="[382,418,1738,1764]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" value="0.5">0.5</number>
length of apophyses posteriores, curved, stout. Ostium bursae rhomboidal, with folded and sclerotised margins derived from caudal margin of sternum 
<number box="[918,933,1776,1802]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" value="8.0">8</number>
which is deeply incised mesally, width of incision about 
<number box="[322,373,1815,1841]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" value="0.25">0.25</number>
distance between bases of apophyses anteriores; antrum absent. In length colliculum equal to apophyses anteriores; ductus seminalis narrow, tubular, joined cephalically to colliculum. Ductus bursae membranous, straight and tubular, 
<number box="[589,628,1893,1919]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times length of apophyses posteriores. Corpus bursae pyriform, medially densely covered with small internal spines; signum in caudal 
<number box="[1013,1066,1931,1957]" pageId="3" pageNumber="19" value="0.25">0.25</number>
of corpus bursae, boomerangshaped and dentate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
